--   Represents a ACK message structure (see chapter 2.13.1). This structure contains the 
--   following elements: 
--
--  #####################################  
-- 		                 --  1: MSH (Message Header)   
-- 		                 --  2: SFT (Software Segment) optional repeating

-- 		                 --  3: UAC (User Authentication Credential Segment) optional  
-- 		                 --  4: MSA (Message Acknowledgment)   
-- 		                 --  5: ERR (Error) optional  
-- 		                 --  6: QAK (Query Acknowledgment) optional  
-- 		                 --  7: QRD (Original-Style Query Definition)   
-- 		                 --  8: QRF (Original style query filter) optional  
-- 		                 --  9: ADR_A19_QUERY_RESPONSE (a Group object)  repeating 
-- 		                 --  10: DSC (Continuation Pointer) optional

--  --  Represents a DFT_P11_COMMON_ORDER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order) optional  
--                          --  2: DFT_P11_TIMING_QUANTITY (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: DFT_P11_ORDER (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  4: DFT_P11_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a DFT_P11_FINANCIAL group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: FT1 (Financial Transaction)   
--                          --  2: DFT_P11_FINANCIAL_PROCEDURE (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: DFT_P11_FINANCIAL_COMMON_ORDER (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: DRG (Diagnosis Related Group) optional  
--                          --  6: GT1 (Guarantor) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: DFT_P11_FINANCIAL_INSURANCE (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --

--                          --  4: EHC_E20_DIAGNOSIS (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: OBX (Observation-- Result) optional repeating choice
--  --  
--  --  
--  --  Note that this structure has "choice" elements. This means that one of the 
--  --  structures above marked as "choice" must be present, but no more than one.
--  --   
--  --  
--  
--  --

--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: IN1 (Insurance)   
--                          --  2: IN2 (Insurance Additional Information) optional  
--                          --  3: IN3 (Insurance Additional Information, Certification) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMB_O27_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBX (Observation-- Result)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMB_O27_ORDER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order)   
--                          --  2: OMB_O27_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: BPO (Blood product order)   
--                          --  4: SPM (Specimen) optional  
--                          --  5: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: OMB_O27_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  8: FT1 (Financial Transaction) optional repeating 
--                          --  9: BLG (Billing) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMB_O27_PATIENT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PID (Patient Identification)   
--                          --  2: PD1 (Patient Additional Demographic) optional  
--                          --  3: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: OMB_O27_PATIENT_VISIT (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  5: OMB_O27_INSURANCE (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: GT1 (Guarantor) optional  
--                          --  7: AL1 (Patient Allergy Information) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --

--                          --  2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional

--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMS_O05_INSURANCE group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: IN1 (Insurance)   
--                          --  2: IN2 (Insurance Additional Information) optional  
--                          --  3: IN3 (Insurance Additional Information, Certification) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMS_O05_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBX (Observation-- Result)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OMS_O05_ORDER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order)   
--                          --  2: OMS_O05_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: RQD (Requisition Detail)   
--                          --  4: RQ1 (Requisition Detail-1) optional  
--                          --  5: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: OMS_O05_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: BLG (Billing) optional  
--  --  
--  --

--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PID (Patient Identification)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORG_O20_RESPONSE group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORG_O20_PATIENT (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  2: ORG_O20_ORDER (a Group object)  repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORG_O20_SPECIMEN group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: SPM (Specimen)   
--                          --  2: SAC (Specimen Container detail) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORG_O20_TIMING group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORI_O24_ORDER group structure (a Group object).

--  --  This Group contains the following elements:

--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order)   
--                          --  2: ORI_O24_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: OBR (Observation Request)   
--                          --  4: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: ROL (Role) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: IPC (Imaging Procedure Control Segment)  repeating

--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: IN1 (Insurance)   
--                          --  2: IN2 (Insurance Additional Information) optional  
--                          --  3: IN3 (Insurance Additional Information, Certification) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORM_O01_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.

--  --  Represents a ORM_O01_ORDER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order)   
--                          --  2: ORM_O01_ORDER_DETAIL (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  3: FT1 (Financial Transaction) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: CTI (Clinical Trial Identification) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: BLG (Billing) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORM_O01_ORDER_DETAIL group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBR (Observation Request)   choice
--                          --  2: RQD (Requisition Detail)   choice
--                          --  3: RQ1 (Requisition Detail-1)   choice
--                          --  4: RXO (Pharmacy-- Treatment Order)   choice
--                          --  5: ODS (Dietary Orders, Supplements, and Preferences)   choice
--                          --  6: ODT (Diet Tray Instructions)   choice
--                          --  7: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  8: CTD (Contact Data) optional  
--                          --  9: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating 
--                          --  10: ORM_O01_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  --  Note that this structure has "choice" elements. This means that one of the 
--  --  structures above marked as "choice" must be present, but no more than one.
--  --   
--  --  
--  
--  --

--  --  Represents a ORU_R01_PATIENT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PID (Patient Identification)   
--                          --  2: PD1 (Patient Additional Demographic) optional  
--                          --  3: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: NK1 (Next of Kin --  Associated Parties) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: OBX (Observation-- Result) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: ORU_R01_VISIT (a Group object) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R01_PATIENT_RESULT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORU_R01_PATIENT (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  2: ORU_R01_ORDER_OBSERVATION (a Group object)  repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R01_SPECIMEN group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: SPM (Specimen)   
--                          --  2: OBX (Observation-- Result) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R01_TIMING_QTY group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R01_VISIT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PV1 (Patient Visit)   
--                          --  2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R30_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBX (Observation-- Result)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R30_TIMING_QTY group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a ORU_R30_VISIT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PV1 (Patient Visit)   
--                          --  2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OSR_Q06_ORDER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ORC (Common Order)   
--                          --  2: OSR_Q06_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: OBR (Observation Request)   choice
--                          --  4: RQD (Requisition Detail)   choice
--                          --  5: RQ1 (Requisition Detail-1)   choice
--                          --  6: RXO (Pharmacy-- Treatment Order)   choice
--                          --  7: ODS (Dietary Orders, Supplements, and Preferences)   choice
--                          --  8: ODT (Diet Tray Instructions)   choice
--                          --  9: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  10: CTI (Clinical Trial Identification) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  --  Note that this structure has "choice" elements. This means that one of the 
--  --  structures above marked as "choice" must be present, but no more than one.
--  --   
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OSR_Q06_PATIENT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PID (Patient Identification)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OSR_Q06_RESPONSE group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OSR_Q06_PATIENT (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  2: OSR_Q06_ORDER (a Group object)  repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OSR_Q06_TIMING group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R21_CONTAINER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: SAC (Specimen Container detail)   
--                          --  2: SID (Substance Identifier) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R21_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBX (Observation-- Result) optional  
--                          --  2: TCD (Test Code Detail) optional  
--                          --  3: SID (Substance Identifier) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R21_ORDER_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OUL_R21_CONTAINER (a Group object) optional  
--                          --  2: ORC (Common Order) optional  
--                          --  3: OBR (Observation Request)   
--                          --  4: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: OUL_R21_TIMING_QTY (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: OUL_R21_OBSERVATION (a Group object)  repeating 
--                          --  7: CTI (Clinical Trial Identification) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R21_PATIENT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PID (Patient Identification)   
--                          --  2: PD1 (Patient Additional Demographic) optional  
--                          --  3: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: OUL_R21_VISIT (a Group object) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R21_TIMING_QTY group structure (a Group object).

--                          --  2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R22_CONTAINER group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: SAC (Specimen Container detail)   
--                          --  2: INV (Inventory Detail) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a OUL_R22_ORDER group structure (a Group object).

--                          --  7: CTI (Clinical Trial Identification) optional repeating

--                          --  5: OBX (Observation-- Result) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating

--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: RXE (Pharmacy-- Treatment Encoded Order)   
--                          --  2: PEX_P07_TIMING_QTY (a Group object)  repeating 
--                          --  3: RXR (Pharmacy-- Treatment Route) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PEX_P07_STUDY group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: CSR (Clinical Study Registration)   
--                          --  2: CSP (Clinical Study Phase) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PEX_P07_TIMING_QTY group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PEX_P07_VISIT group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: PV1 (Patient Visit)   
--                          --  2: PV2 (Patient Visit - Additional Information) optional  
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PGL_PC6_GOAL group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: GOL (Goal Detail)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: VAR (Variance) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: PGL_PC6_GOAL_ROLE (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: PGL_PC6_PATHWAY (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: PGL_PC6_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: PGL_PC6_PROBLEM (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  8: PGL_PC6_ORDER (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --

--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBR (Observation Request)   choice
--                          --  2: Hxx (any HL7 segment)   choice
--                          --  3: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: VAR (Variance) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: PGL_PC6_ORDER_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  --  Note that this structure has "choice" elements. This means that one of the 
--  --  structures above marked as "choice" must be present, but no more than one.

--                          --  5: PPR_PC1_PATHWAY (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: PPR_PC1_PROBLEM_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: PPR_PC1_GOAL (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  8: PPR_PC1_ORDER (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PPR_PC1_PROBLEM_OBSERVATION group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBX (Observation-- Result)   
--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents a PPR_PC1_PROBLEM_ROLE group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: ROL (Role)   
--                          --  2: VAR (Variance) optional repeating

--                          --  2: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  3: VAR (Variance) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: PPT_PCL_GOAL_ROLE (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: PPT_PCL_GOAL_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  6: PPT_PCL_PROBLEM (a Group object) optional repeating 
--                          --  7: PPT_PCL_ORDER (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --

--  --

--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.

--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: OBR (Observation Request)   choice
--                          --  2: Hxx (any HL7 segment)   choice
--                          --  3: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating 
--                          --  4: VAR (Variance) optional repeating 
--                          --  5: PPT_PCL_ORDER_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating 
--  --  
--  --  
--  --  Note that this structure has "choice" elements. This means that one of the 
--  --  structures above marked as "choice" must be present, but no more than one.

--  --  Represents a RDS_O13_TIMING group structure (a Group object).
--  --  A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in-- excluded together.
--  --  This Group contains the following elements:  
--  --  
--  --  
--                          --  1: TQ1 (Timing-- Quantity)   
--                          --  2: TQ2 (Timing-- Quantity Relationship) optional repeating

--   #############
--   hl7 data type
--    
--   Represents an HL7 AD (Address) data type. 
--   This type consists of the following components:
--   
--   ######################  
--  --  Street Address (ST)
--  --  Other Designation (ST)
--  --  City (ST)
--  --  State or Province (ST)
--  --  Zip or Postal Code (ST)
--  --  Country (ID)
--  --  Address Type (ID)
--  --  Other Geographic Designation (ST)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 AUI (Authorization Information) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Authorization Number (ST)
--  --  Date (DT)
--  --  Source (ST)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 CCD (Charge Code and Date) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Invocation Event (ID)
--  --  Date-- time (DTM)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 CCP (Channel Calibration Parameters) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Channel Calibration Sensitivity Correction Factor (NM)
--  --  Channel Calibration Baseline (NM)
--  --  Channel Calibration Time Skew (NM)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 CD (Channel Definition) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Channel Identifier (WVI)
--  --  Waveform Source (WVS)
--  --  Channel Sensitivity and Units (CSU)
--  --  Channel Calibration Parameters (CCP)
--  --  Channel Sampling Frequency (NM)
--  --  Minimum and Maximum Data Values (NR)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 CE (Coded Element) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Identifier (NULLDT)
--  --  Text (NULLDT)
--  --  Name of Coding System (NULLDT)
--  --  Alternate Identifier (NULLDT)
--  --  Alternate Text (NULLDT)
--  --  Name of Alternate Coding System (NULLDT)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 CF (Coded Element with Formatted Values) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Identifier (ST)
--  --  Formatted Text (FT)
--  --  Name of Coding System (ID)

--  --  Value Code (CNE)
--  --  Value Amount (MO)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 VH (Visiting Hours) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Start Day Range (ID)
--  --  End Day Range (ID)
--  --  Start Hour Range (TM)
--  --  End Hour Range (TM)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 VID (Version Identifier) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Version ID (ID)
--  --  Internationalization Code (CWE)
--  --  International Version ID (CWE)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 VR (Value Range) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  First Data Code Value (ST)
--  --  Last Data Code Value (ST)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --  
--  --  Represents an HL7 WVI (Channel Identifier) data type. 
--  --  This type consists of the following components:
--  --  
--  --  Channel Number (NM)
--  --  Channel Name (ST)
--  --  
--  --  
--  
--  --

--  --  Source One Name (ST)
--  --  Source Two Name (ST)
--  --  
--  --

--  --  Other Designation (ST)
--  --  City (ST)
--  --  State or Province (ST)

--  --  County-- Parish Code (IS)
--  --  Census Tract (IS)

--  --  Family Name (FN)
--  --  Given Name (ST)

-- User    Abnormal flags 
-- 0078    <  Below absolute low-off instrument scale 
-- 0078    >  Above absolute high-off instrument scale 
-- 0078    A  Abnormal (applies to non-numeric results) 
-- 0078    AA  Very abnormal (applies to non-numeric units, analogous to panic limitsfor numeric units) 
-- 0078    B  Better-- use when direction not relevant 
-- 0078    D  Significant change down 
-- 0078    H  Above high normal 
-- 0078    HH  Above upper panic limits 
-- 0078    I  Intermediate. Indicates for microbiology susceptibilities only. 
-- 0078    L  Below low normal 
-- 0078    LL  Below lower panic limits 
-- 0078    MS  Moderately susceptible. Indicates for microbiology susceptibilities only. 
-- 0078    N  Normal (applies to non-numeric results) 
-- 0078    null  No range defined,or normal ranges don't apply 
-- 0078    R  Resistant. Indicates for microbiology susceptibilities only. 
-- 0078    S  Susceptible. Indicates for microbiology susceptibilities only. 
-- 0078    U  Significant change up 
-- 0078    VS  Very susceptible. Indicates for microbiology susceptibilities only. 
-- 0078    W  Worse-- use when direction not relevant 
-- 
-- 
-- HL7    Nature of Abnormal Testing 
-- 0080    A  An age-based population 
-- 0080    B  Breed 
-- 0080    N  None - generic normal range 
-- 0080    R  A race-based population 
-- 0080    S  A sex-based population 
-- 0080    SP  Species 
-- 0080    ST  Strain

-- HL7    Observation result status codes interpretation 
-- 0085    C  Record coming over is a correction and thus replaces a final result 
-- 0085    D  Deletes the OBX record 
-- 0085    F  Final results; Can only be changed with a corrected result. 
-- 0085    I  Specimen in lab; results pending 
-- 0085    N  Not asked; used to affirmatively document that the observation identified in the OBX was not sought when the universal service ID in OBR-4 implies that it would be sought. 
-- 0085    O  Order detail description only (no result) 
-- 0085    P  Preliminary results 
-- 0085    R  Results entered --  not verified 
-- 0085    S  Partial results. Deprecated. Retained only for backward compatibility as of V2.6. 
-- 0085    U  Results status change to final without retransmitting results already sent as 'preliminary.' E.g., radiology changes status from preliminary to final 
-- 0085    W  Post original as wrong, e.g., transmitted for wrong patient 
-- 0085    X  Results cannot be obtained for this observation

-- 
-- HL7    Response level 
-- 0179    AL  Always. All MFA segments (whether denoting errors or not) must be returned via the applicationlevel acknowledgment message 
-- 0179    ER  Error-- Reject conditions only. Only MFA segments denoting errors must be returned via the application-level acknowledgment for this message 
-- 0179    NE  Never. No application-level response needed 
-- 0179    SU  Success. Only MFA segments denoting success must be returned via the application-level acknowledgment for this message 
-- 
-- HL7    Record-level event code 
-- 0180    MAC  Reactivate deactivated record

-- 0180    MUP  Update record for master file

-- 0299    A  No encoding - data are displayable ASCII characters. 
-- 0299    Base64  Encoding as defined by MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) standard RFC 1521. Four consecutive ASCII characters represent three consecutive octets of binary data. Base64 utilizes a 65-character subset of US-ASCII, consisting of both the upper and 
-- 0299    Hex  Hexadecimal encoding - consecutive pairs of hexadecimal digits represent consecutive single octets.

-- User    Namespace ID 
-- 0300    ...  No suggested values defined

-- HL7    Universal ID type 
-- 0301    DNS  An Internet dotted name. Either in ASCII or as integers 
-- 0301    GUID  Same as UUID. 
-- 0301    HCD  The CEN Healthcare Coding Scheme Designator. (Identifiers used in DICOM follow this assignment scheme.) 
-- 0301    HL7  Reserved for future HL7 registration schemes

-- 0335    QSHIFT  during each of three eight-hour shifts at institution-specified times
